# SDAD v5 -- line-ending policy (repo has core.autocrlf=true on Windows).
# Shell scripts MUST stay LF: a CRLF shebang/line breaks sh on checkout
# ("bad interpreter"), the same failure class as the L-01 ratchet and the
# install.ps1 pre-commit CRLF->LF fix. Applies to hooks, checks, installers.
*.sh text eol=lf

# PowerShell tolerates CRLF; leave .ps1 to the default so the ASCII ratchet
# (bytes > 127) is unaffected -- CR/LF are both ASCII.
